2026-05-25 | Check if Array Contains Complete Range

	Question
Return true if all range elements exist.
	Key Insight
Fast lookup is needed for checking presence.
Hash set allows:
		O(1) average lookup.
	Approach
1.	Insert all array elements into hash set  
2.	Traverse numbers from:
		start → end
3.	If any number missing:
		return false
4.	If all found:
		return true
	Time Complexity
	O(n + (end-start+1))
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsRange(vector<int>& arr,
                       int start,
                       int end) {
        unordered_set<int> st(arr.begin(),
                              arr.end());
        for(int x = start; x <= end; x++){
            if(!st.count(x))
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Hashing converts repeated searching:
		from O(n)
		to O(1) average time  
This makes range verification efficient.
